'''Mercedes Brignone''' (18 May 1885 – 24 June 1967) was a Spanish-born Italian [[stage actor|stage]], [[film actor|film]] and [[television actress]]. She was the daughter of the actor [[Giuseppe Brignone]]. She often played [[divas]], and appeared in numerous [[silent films]] for [[Milano Films]] during the 1910s.<ref>Moliterno p.207</ref> In later years she played largely [[supporting role]]s. She was the older sister of film director and actor [[Guido Brignone]] and the aunt of actress [[Lilla Brignone]].

